cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.HC 

The paper proposes a novel framework for gait recognition using AutoEncoder and LSTM-based integration. This involves disentangling pose and appearance features from RGB imagery, which falls under computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The paper also mentions collecting a new dataset, which involves human-computer interaction (cs.HC) and multimedia (cs.MM) sub-categories. Finally, the proposed method demonstrates superior performance to state-of-the-art methods, which involves artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category.
